abstract: "laserbeamsize is a Python library for analyzing laser beam quality according\
  \ to the ISO 11146 standard. It provides tools for calculating beam center, diameter,\
  \ divergence, and M\xB2 parameter from beam profile images. The package implements\
  \ variance-based beam size calculations, background noise handling, and beam propagation\
  \ analysis for TEM00 and higher-order modes. It is intended for education, research,\
  \ and engineering applications in laser metrology and beam characterization."
